<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-06-15T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-06-15T18:00:00-05:00" n="220" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d220">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">893.102 Tientsin/252: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Chargé in Japan</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Dooman</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-06-15T19:00:00-04:00">June 15, 1939—7
                                    p.m.</date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>165. Your 274, June 15, 5 p.m.</p>
                            <list>
                                <label>1.</label>
                                <item>The Department appreciates the information and thoughtful
                                    comment given in your telegram under reference.</item>
                                <label>2.</label>
                                <item>With regard to paragraph 6 of your telegram, the Department
                                    approves the position you have taken and assumes that you have
                                    informed the British Ambassador of that position.</item>
                                <label>3.</label>
                                <item>Please repeat your telegram to Peiping with the request that
                                    Peiping closely paraphrase it and communicate it by radio in
                                    another confidential code to Chungking and Tientsin.</item>
                            </list>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>